Exercise 5:

1.
Z(3,33,92,010) is the difference between the time when the website started sending the packets of file and the time the website send that the file is completely sent. Wget take the difference of these times.
Y(10.8MB/s) is the avergae speed which can be find out by dividing Z with X.
X(3.0s) is the total size of packets(segments) of file received[].

#############################################################################################
2.
Throughput=Y*8(Mega Bits per second)=10.8*8Mbps=86.4Mbps
We are connected to 100Mbps Ethernet LAN.

##############################################################################################
3.
Time was calculated by taking difference between the time of ping request and reply.

